  "pages": [
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "text": "With budding blocks in mind you designed the Crystallarieum: an Ink-powered contraption that grows chunks of raw ore and mundane gemstones into sparkling crystals.$(br)Even though you failed to grow real $(l:general/shards)gems$(/l) despite all your efforts, you quickly realized that it could grow all sorts of other resources instead."
    },
    {
      "type": "spectrum:pedestal_crafting",
      "title": "Pedestal Recipe",
      "recipe": "spectrum:pedestal/tier4/crystallarieum",
      "text": "Requires a color of Ink depending on the resource you grow. It fits a stack of catalysts, which it uses to enhance the growth process. For a few rare materials that even may be required."
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "title": "Growing Metals",
      "text": "Metallic resources require unrefined materials such as $(item)Raw Iron$(), resulting in a $(item)Small Iron Bud$() that will grow steadily until it reaches maturity and can be safely harvested."
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "title": "Growing Crystals",
      "text": "Crystals such as $(item)Diamonds$() require more Ink, but their nature allows you to grow them over and over again - $(item)Diamond Clusters$() yieling more $(item)Diamonds$()."
    },
